options.query: host="jfrog-cloud" service=jfrog.saas.rt.artifactory.request | timechart count by return_status
host="jfrog-cloud" AND return_status=200
host="jfrog-cloud" service=jfrog.saas.rt.artifactory.request return_status=4* | timechart count by return_status
host="jfrog-cloud" service=jfrog.saas.rt.artifactory.request return_status=5* | timechart count by return_status

host="jfrog-cloud" service=jfrog.saas.rt.artifactory.request remote_address!="127.0.0.1" | top remote_address 
|  head limit=10
host="jfrog-cloud" log_type="artifactory-request" user_name!="non_authenticated_user" user_name!="token:*@*" | top user_name by return_status
host="jfrog-cloud" log_type="artifactory-request" | timechart count by return_status
host="jfrog-cloud" service=jfrog.saas.rt.artifactory.request user_name!="non_authenticated_user" user_name!="token:*@*" | top user_name
host="jfrog-cloud" | top service

host="jfrog-cloud" request_url NOT (/api*system* OR /api/*/metrics* OR /api/system* OR /api/auth/* OR /api/storageinfo* OR /api/replications OR /api/jobs/replications OR /api/xray* OR /api/repositories* OR /api/retention/link OR /ui/treebrowser OR /ui/* OR /api/docker/public-images/v2/token) |  top request_url 
|  head limit=10

host="jfrog-cloud" repo!="" | top repo 
|  head limit=10
host="jfrog-cloud" repo!="" | top image
host="jfrog-cloud" repo!="" | timechart count by repo
host="jfrog-cloud" repo!="" | timechart count by repo

host="jfrog-cloud" repo!="" | top image
|  head limit=10
host="jfrog-cloud" repo!="NULL" repo!="" image!="NULL" | timechart count by image
host="jfrog-cloud" service=jfrog.saas.rt.access.security.audit user_name!=UNKNOWN | stats count by user_name
host="jfrog-cloud" service=jfrog.saas.rt.access.security.audit event=TKN |  timechart count by event_type
host="jfrog-cloud" service=jfrog.saas.rt.access.security.audit event=PRM |  timechart count by event_type
host="jfrog-cloud" service=jfrog.saas.rt.access.security.audit event=USR |  timechart count by event_type
host="jfrog-cloud" service=jfrog.saas.rt.access.security.audit event=GRP |  timechart count by event_type
host="jfrog-cloud" service=jfrog.saas.rt.artifactory.access | top action_response

host="jfrog-cloud" service=jfrog.saas.rt.access.security.audit user_name!=UNKNOWN | stats count by user_name

host="jfrog-cloud" service=jfrog.saas.rt.artifactory.access action_response=DENIED* user_name!=NA | top ip_address

description: This dashboard provides a high-level summary of the usage of the JFrog Artifactory Cloud instance. This includes an overview of access requests, audit events and access logs as well as a summary of various operations performed on JFrog Artifactory.
title: JFrog Platform Cloud Log Analytics
